You never told me it was across the pond.
I can't reach the rope. I don't know what to do...
I'll have to ask someone how to cross...
There are stakes in the ground. Can we use them?
You did it!We can cross now!
There's a stone monument. We'll be safe here!
Do you want to consume the bonfire set and rest?
Huh?I don't have any of those.
We'll consume one bonfire set, if that's all right.

After an event involving a change in movement speed, the speed will return to normal.
Shh!I'm in a good place right now.
You again. What are you doing here?
No way, you're going to help me again.
What kind of intuition is that?
I mean, he was in trouble, but...
Actually, a flintlock gun I got before.
I don't know how to apologize.
Do you have a musket or something?
If you have it, would you mind talking to me again?
I'll stick with the trap until then.
What do you mean, good luck catching him?
You know what I'm talking about!
What, you want to talk to me to pass the time?
That's nice of you to say, but that's mean!
The beast will flee at the sound of your voice!
Oh, a musket gun!This is it!Here!
Thank you. As usual, you won't be able to use your gun.
You brought it for me, didn't you?
I don't know, the beast used a recovery item and ran away...
He didn't have a bandage on, but he was making a bandaging gesture, okay?
I don't have a choice. Let's change places...
And if they recover in the meantime, what's the point? Why not!
Do you mind if I borrow this gun for a while?
I'll thank you some other time.
You, too. Have a safe trip. Bye.
I can move the log from here!
I don't think we can move him.
